  <brief_title>Comparison of Post-operative Pain at Umbilical Wound After Laparoscopic Cholecystectomy With Transumbilical Versus Infraumbilical Incision</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Thammasat University</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Thammasat University</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study compare outcomes (i.e. pain, wound infection, and patient satisfaction) between
      infra-umbilical vs. trans-umbilical incision after Laparoscopic cholecystectomy
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Infra-umbilical wound have been used for a while with aim at improving cosmoses of the
      incision. Formerly, standard incision for laparoscopic cholecystectomy was infra-umbilical
      wound. However, no study directly compare these types of incisions in term of postoperative
      pain, wound infection, and patient satisfaction.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
